==English==

===Etymology===
{{OE.}} ''[[cruschen]], [[crousshen]]'', {{OF.}} ''[[cruisir]], [[croissir]]'', from {{LL.}} ''[[cruscire]]'', probably of Germanic origin, from a derivative of the word seen in {{Goth.}} ''[[kruistan]]'' to gnash; akin to {{Sw.}} ''[[krysta]]'' to squeeze, {{Dan.}} ''[[kryste]]'', {{Icel.}} ''[[kreysta]]''.

